# Phishing Case Study: VIT Student's Scholarship Scam (2023)

## Crime Overview

Phishing is a cybercrime where attackers impersonate trusted entities to steal sensitive data such as login credentials, bank details, or Aadhaar numbers via deceptive emails or SMS.

# How It Happens (Step-by-Step)

Victim receives an urgent email/SMS from a fake "VIT Scholarships Office" (spoofed sender: scholarships@vitbhopal.co.in).

Message claims: "Congratulations! Claim your ₹10,000 scholarship—verify via link before deadline."

Link leads to a cloned VIT login page (vitbhopal-login[.]com) requesting ID, password, and UPI PIN.

Victim enters details; attackers harvest data in real-time.

Stolen information is used for account takeovers, UPI fraud, or identity theft.

## Targets

College students (18–22 years), especially in India.

Lured by scholarships, internships, or fee waivers.

VIT Bhopal reported 15+ cases in 2023 (Times of India, Oct 2023; cybercrime.gov.in reports).

## Consequences

One VIT forensic chemistry student lost ₹45,000 via unauthorized UPI transfers.

Faced credit score damage and weeks resolving identity theft.

Emotional toll included anxiety; academic impact included delayed projects.

Nationally, phishing caused ₹1,300 crore losses in 2023 (RBI data).

Victims often face legal scrutiny if stolen identities are misused for further crimes.

3# Key Takeaway:
Phishing scams exploit urgency and trust. Students must verify sources, avoid clicking suspicious links, and report incidents promptly to prevent financial and personal damage.
